This paper proposes a distributed architecture for deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The architecture involves actors interacting with their own instances of the environment and accumulating experience in a shared memory, which suggests a distributed computing aspect (cs.DC). The use of prioritized experience replay is a technique commonly used in reinforcement learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses achieving better performance in a shorter amount of time, which could be considered a systems aspect (cs.SY).
